  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Achieving advocacy results in 10 Vietnamese provinces: Piloting FACT</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is aimed at improving and systematizing the lobby and advocacy capacities of 40 staff and leaders from 10 provinces by piloting the FACT tool of Agriterra in the year 2015. This is in line with the conducted workshop in December 2014 when the first FACT (Farmer Advocacy Consultation Tool) workshop took place in Hanoi, Vietnam. Furthermore, the proposal aims at setting a more clear lobby-agenda for 10 provinces and VNFU leaders and staff.

Also three consecutive workshops will be organised by Agriterra and VNFU in August or September 2015 to discuss the lessons-learnt of using FACT, train new Trainers in rolling out FACT in their provinces, and discuss, share and improve the lobby agendas for the next year(s) between the 10 provinces.

VNFU considers one of its main goals the monitoring of the existing guidelines, policies, and laws related to agriculture, farmers, rural areas. And to see if these are well and correctly implemented, and to work out proposals to amend existing legislation by participating in lobby and advocacy to make sure policies and laws are close to the reality and aspirations of farmers, members of VNFU. 

This should lead to creating favourable conditions for farmers to develop production, business and improve their life. 

With this project VNFU is trying to improve their lobby capacities by:
1. using FACT in 10 provinces in a pilot, 
2. organising a FACT workshop to share lessons learnt
3. Train FACT-trainers to spread the use of FACT. To systematize lobbying and advocacy on all levels within VNFU (FACT).
4.	Sharpening the lobby agenda and priorities for the future by organising an agenda-setting workshop.

The project will focus on the 10 provinces of which 40 staff and leaders were trained during the preparatory workshop in December 2014 by Agriterra. The target groups are farmers who will be consulted about their needs during the pilot phase, and VNFU staff and leaders, especially the ones at sub-national level (grass-root, district, provincial level) who are directly involved in policy advocacy. 

They will be reached in the pilot phase by the 40 VNFU staff and leaders who are carrying out the pilot of the FACT workshop of December 2014. Also the project will provide platforms for all stakeholders on sub-national level to share the mutual understanding of FACT, and the real needs of farmers. 

The project will seek for the technical support and advise from Agriterra and other capable agencies during the implementation of the project. By the end of the project, the obtained knowledge and experiences will stay in VNFU and expanded by VNFU staffs and leaders.

Goal is to improve the advocacy capacities of staff and leaders from 10 Vietnamese provinces in the year 2015</narrative>
  </description>
